The paper discusses a method for optimising expensive black-box functions using Bayesian optimisation, which is a popular technique in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The method involves finding a region of design space that is insensitive to the inputs, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions using an evolutionary algorithm to optimise the expectation of improvements, which is a common technique in optimisation and search algorithms (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the method on test functions, which is a common practice in data science and machine learning (cs.DS).
